Henry DAVIS, Appellant, v. A. C. ADERHOLD, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Atlanta, Georgia, Appellee. No. 7362. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 16, 1934. In forma pauperis. Henry Davis, of Atlanta, Ga., in pro. per. Lawrence S. Camp, U. S. Atty., and H. T. Nichols, Sp. Atty., both of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before BRYAN, FOSTER, and SIBLEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
